gly faced obstacles to their legislative intentions, nascent disability advocacy and protest groups took the cause to the American people forming the basis of the contemporary disability rights movement. Drawing on extensive archival material, Pettinicchio redefines the relationship between grassroots advocacy and institutional politics, revealing a cycle of progress and backlash embedded in the American political system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPeople with disabilitiesxCivil rightszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPeople with disabilitiesxGovernment policyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPeople with disabilitiesxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aSocial movementszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / People with Disabilities.2bisacsh  adisability rights.  anonprofit organizations.  apolicy retrenchment.  apolicy-participation cycle.  apolitical entrepreneurs.  apolitical process.  aprotest.  asocial movements.  asocial policy.  awelfare state.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360977840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503609778423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503609778.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK 